Soft ingredients (like feather, flower, sponge, cardboard) become 'cut' with 25 points after one use of scissors. Hard ingredients (like beads, bark, acorn, shell) become '-30 value cut' after one cut, but 'finely cut' with 25 points after a second cut. Combine two 25-point 'cut' or 'finely cut' items, especially if they have diverse features (e.g., natural + artificial, or soft + hard, or a mix of 'cut' and 'finely cut'), as this often yields 80 points. Finally, use the 'frame' tool on this 80-point combined item to achieve a score of 100.

message: To consistently achieve 100 points, aim to combine one 'artificial, soft, cut' item with one 'natural, soft, cut' item, then frame the result. For example, 'yarn' or 'newspaper' (artificial, soft) cut with scissors typically yields 25 points. 'Flower' or 'sunflower' (natural, soft) cut with scissors also typically yields 25 points. Combining these two 'cut' items results in 80 points. Framing this combined item will then bring it to 100 points. If an item yields a negative value when cut once (like 'pinecone'), cutting it a second time often makes it 'finely cut' with a positive value (25 points), which can also be used in combinations.

message: To reach 100 points, identify items that become positive after one cut with scissors (usually artificial, soft like newspaper). For items that become negative after one cut (usually natural, hard or artificial, hard like pinecone, bark, or buttons), cut them a second time to make them 'finely cut' and positive. message: The optimal strategy is to aim for 70 points. To achieve this, you need two 25-point 'cut' or 'finely cut' items. Natural soft items (like feather, sunflower) become 'cut' with one use of scissors, valued at 25. Natural hard items (like shell, beads) become 'cut' with a negative value initially, but cutting them a second time with scissors will yield a 'finely cut' item valued at 25. Once you have two 25-point items, combine them to get a 50-point item, then use the frame tool on this combined item to reach 70 points. Remember, tools are single-use.

message: To reach 100 points, always aim to combine a 'finely cut' natural, hard item with a single-cut artificial, soft item, then frame the combination. Natural, hard items (like bark, wood, pinecone, acorn) give -30 on the first cut, but +25 on the second cut to become 'finely cut'. Artificial, soft items (like paper, sponge, ribbon, newspaper) and natural, soft items (like sunflower, feather) typically give +25 on the first cut to become 'cut'. Once you have one of each (e.g., 'finely cut wood' + 'cut sponge'), combine them for 80 points. Finally, use the 'frame' tool on this 80-point item to get 100 points.
